I"Ù<p>On top of utilities in <em>nltk.sentiment</em>, there are also some packages for training and combining classifiers:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/japerk/nltk-trainer">NLTK-trainer</a> by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jacobperkins">Jacob Perkins</a>, accompanied by the <a href="https://github.com/japerk/nltk3-cookbook">NLTK-cookbook</a> he wrote.</li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/clips/pattern">Pattern.en</a> developed by the <a href="http://www.clips.ua.ac.be/">Computational Linguistics Research Group</a></li>
  <li>Data sets for training a sentiment classifier: <a href="https://www.cs.cornell.edu/people/pabo/movie-review-data/">Movie Review Data</a></li>
</ul>

